{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"899f7b8f-c568-4a1d-a82f-99b8893553ad","content":"Here's what you need to change to upgrade to MSTest v3:\n\n**In `TestProject.csproj`:**\n\n1. **Remove** the old assembly reference to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework`\n2. **Add** the `MSTest` v3 NuGet package (it's now a single meta-package)\n3. **Update** `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` to a current version\n\n```xml\n<ItemGroup>\n  <PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.8.3\" />\n  <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk\" Version=\"17.12.0\" />\n</ItemGroup>\n```\n\n**In your test code:** No changes needed — MSTest v3 still uses the same `Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.UnitTesting` namespace, and `[TestClass]`, `[TestMethod]`, `[Timeout]`, and `Assert.*` all carry over.\n\n**Summary of changes:**\n- Remove the `<Reference Include=\"Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework\" />` line\n- Replace with `MSTest` v3 package (which bundles the framework + adapter)\n- Bump `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk`\n\nWould you like me to apply these changes?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"55574564-6f9b-44da-92ca-59ceeb75bef9","outputTokens":316,"requestId":"BC27:A067E:1F5FE27:23213A5:69FAA683"},"id":"f46917b9-67dd-445b-a23d-31cc983d45fe","timestamp":"2026-05-06T02:25:14.210Z","parentId":"7689de69-b233-4c5d-a3b9-0fb3ab775f70"}
